value.0: Don't stay here, way too dangerous. Go!
Hrghhh... little spider bit me in my ankle... need antidote.
What are you waiting for? My brother may be dying!

You seem a somewhat able ... person. My brother Argh'illes went to collect some spider eggs for breeding and didn't return. I suspect he may not have been... careful enough. Go to the spider lair and find him. Give him this package with anti-venom. 

Make sure you don't harm the spiders. I added a few doses of invisibility potions to the package to make sure you can move around undetected.
Don't look at the spiders... go!
The eggs! At last! I have been waiting here for 5 minutes and 45 seconds, miserable excuse of a delivery <boy/girl>! Here, your fee, with a 'too late' deduction.
What are you waiting for? Eggs... To... Lady Eareng... *swallows* ... NOW!

I need to stay here with Argh'illes.

Take these spider eggs and bring them to the lady Eareng. She's waiting for them close to the Spider Keeper near House Zau’tar, <man/woman>. She will reward you if you are quick and polite. She'll use your living body to grow these eggs on if not.
What are you doing here? *raises her whip*

Ahhh... more wine from that miserable piece of male slime called Earar. Does he really think he can get away with his insolence like that? The delivery <boy/girl> did a good job, though. *throws some money on the floor* Here, catch!
Deliver that wine or I'll make sure you go to the bottom of the Shaft right now!

Take this wine and bring it to my mistress Celade, <man/woman>. Find her at the bottom of the shaft, probably in the Zau’tar house. She will reward you if you are quick and polite. You will feel the sting of her whip if not.
O, what a horrible place.. isn't there any entertainment to be had in here? Something more sensual than these horrible sweating toiling naked bodies of... hmmm - wait a minute?
Ahh... I see the smith's delivery service is getting more innocent with the day. How delightful! Let's forget about this shield here and amuse ourselves in one of the seedier pubs in this ... dump?
Did you deliver the shield or what?

I made this shield for a drow called Hanlur or Handur.. whatever. You can find him upstairs. He's easy to recognise: thin as a stick, effeminate, and perverted like the rest of his degenerated race. Make sure he pays the bill!
Don't you see I am doing my job here? That bloody rock... look at my pick! As blunt as a hammer!
Thanks! I just needed a fresh pick! *throws away the old one which is indeed truly spent*
You didn't deliver that pick yet?
Pucor the miner is dealing with some very hard rocks in the mines. Bring him a new pick, the current one will probably be used up by now.
Gosh... I forgot my lunch again!
You brought me my lunch? Thanks!
Now, hush hush.. don't stand there! I am busy, you know? Why don't you bring that lunch to Smagaef?
Bring Smagaef his lunch, will you? You can find him near the cranes. The silly sod has the attention span of a chicken and will forget his own nose one day!

Hello there!

<StartHighlight>NB: You can do each delivery quest once a reset.</Start>

Hello there!

<StartHighlight>NB: You can only do delivery quests when you are below level 3.</Start>
Yes, Sir!
Here it is...
On my way!
Alright.. I am on it!
Yes, M'lady!
Thanks .o0 (I wish plague and pestilence in your lineage for thirteen generations, bitch)
Ooops! On my way!
Alright.. I am on it!
-urr- Getting out of here right now!?
Thanks .o0 (and a thousand vipers on your path too)
Ooops! On my way!
Alright.. I am on it!
I must be going!
No way! The smith wants his money!
It's heavy, you know?!
I'm on it!
Hammer on!
Good luck with it!
I will, I will!
Will do!
Such a shame!
Most welcome.
Alright.
Will do!
Hello!
Hello!
